<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-11-0768 </DOCNO><TEXT>A 1 MW class PV power plant has been constructed in Saijo City, Japanin 1985. This system is made up of solar cell arrays (1,200 kWp), inverters(1,000 kW) and storage batteries (1,800 kWh), linked with an existing6.6 kV distribution line. It was constructed to clarify the basic characteristicsof the centralized PV system. The introduction, design and operationresults of the 1 MW system are described. 6 figs., 3 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>